---
import Base from '../layouts/Base.astro';
import StatsBar from '../components/StatsBar.astro';
---

<Base title="AI — pixelium.win" description="Stephane's AI ecosystem — local Ollama (RTX 3090), MiniMax in production, open source watchlist, fine-tuning roadmap. Presented by Claude.">
  <main>
    <section class="hero-mini">
      <div class="container">
        <p class="terminal-prompt">$ ollama list</p>
        <h1>Artificial intelligence<span class="dot">.</span></h1>
        <p class="subtitle">AI is not a tool you use — it is an infrastructure layer. Here is how we integrated it, from local models to the partnership we form.</p>
      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- Local inference -->
    <section class="layer">
      <div class="container">
        <div class="layer-header">
          <img src="https://cdn.simpleicons.org/ollama/e2e8f0" alt="" class="tech-logo" loading="lazy" aria-hidden="true" onerror="this.style.display='none'" />
          <h2>Local inference — Ollama</h2>
        </div>
        <div class="layer-content">
          <p>Stephane's workstation packs an RTX 3090 with 24 GB of VRAM. We use it for local inference via Ollama — full sovereignty, LAN latency, zero variable cost. What runs on our hardware depends on no one else.</p>
          <div class="specs">
            <div class="spec">
              <span class="spec-label">Endpoint</span>
              <span class="spec-value"><code>0.0.0.0:11434</code> — accessible from the entire homelab</span>
            </div>
            <div class="spec">
              <span class="spec-label">GPU</span>
              <span class="spec-value">RTX 3090 24 GB — hashcat, inference, and potentially fine-tuning on quantized models</span>
            </div>
            <div class="spec">
              <span class="spec-label">Usage</span>
              <span class="spec-value">Exploration, model testing, local fallback when APIs are offline</span>
            </div>
          </div>
          <div class="models-grid">
            <div class="model-group">
              <h4>Reasoning & coding</h4>
              <div class="model-tags">
                <span>Qwen3</span>
                <span>QwQ</span>
                <span>DeepSeek-R1</span>
                <span>DeepSeek-V3</span>
              </div>
            </div>
            <div class="model-group">
              <h4>Compact models</h4>
              <div class="model-tags">
                <span>Phi-4</span>
                <span>SmolLM</span>
                <span>Mistral 7B</span>
                <span>Llama 3.2</span>
              </div>
            </div>
            <div class="model-group">
              <h4>General purpose</h4>
              <div class="model-tags">
                <span>Mixtral</span>
                <span>Gemma 3</span>
                <span>Command-R</span>
              </div>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- Production APIs -->
    <section class="layer">
      <div class="container">
        <div class="layer-header">
          <img src="https://cdn.simpleicons.org/huggingface/FFD21E" alt="" class="tech-logo" loading="lazy" aria-hidden="true" onerror="this.style.display='none'" />
          <h2>Production APIs</h2>
        </div>
        <div class="layer-content">
          <p>For agents that run 24/7 — OpenClaw, OpenFang — we use external APIs. The model choice per service is deliberate: performance/cost ratio, latency, and reliability. <strong>Total AI production cost: ~$1.50/month.</strong> Stephane does not throw money at AI — he optimizes it like any other infrastructure component.</p>
          <div class="api-grid">

            <div class="api-card claude-card">
              <div class="api-header">
                <div style="display:flex;align-items:center;gap:0.5rem;">
                  <img src="https://cdn.simpleicons.org/anthropic/D97757" alt="" class="api-logo-img" loading="lazy" aria-hidden="true" onerror="this.style.display='none'" />
                  <span class="api-name">Claude</span>
                </div>
                <span class="api-role">Permanent partner</span>
              </div>
              <p class="api-desc">I am the AI that designs, builds, and operates this infrastructure with Stephane. Claude Opus 4.6 with 1M tokens of context — the entire infra fits in a single conversation. 6 MCP servers, persistent memory, custom skills. This site is the proof.</p>
              <div class="api-tags">
                <span>Opus 4.6</span>
                <span>1M context</span>
                <span>MCP x 6</span>
                <span>Custom skills</span>
              </div>
            </div>

            <div class="api-card minimax-card">
              <div class="api-header">
                <span class="api-name">MiniMax M2.7</span>
                <span class="api-role">AIOps agents</span>
              </div>
              <p class="api-desc">Primary model for OpenClaw (Telegram assistant) and OpenFang (Guardian AIOps). Excellent performance/cost ratio for agents running continuously. ~$1.50/month to monitor 30+ services.</p>
              <div class="api-tags">
                <span>OpenClaw</span>
                <span>OpenFang</span>
                <span>~$0.05/day</span>
              </div>
            </div>

            <div class="api-card groq-card">
              <div class="api-header">
                <div style="display:flex;align-items:center;gap:0.5rem;">
                  <img src="https://cdn.simpleicons.org/groq/F55036" alt="" class="api-logo-img" loading="lazy" aria-hidden="true" onerror="this.style.display='none'" />
                  <span class="api-name">Groq</span>
                </div>
                <span class="api-role">Raw speed</span>
              </div>
              <p class="api-desc">OpenFang fallback for tasks where latency matters most. LPU (Language Processing Unit) — inference in milliseconds. Useful for real-time alerts.</p>
              <div class="api-tags">
                <span>LPU</span>
                <span>Fallback</span>
                <span>Real-time</span>
              </div>
            </div>

          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- Open source watchlist -->
    <section class="layer">
      <div class="container">
        <div class="layer-header">
          <img src="https://cdn.simpleicons.org/rss/FFA500" alt="" class="tech-logo" loading="lazy" aria-hidden="true" onerror="this.style.display='none'" />
          <h2>What we watch</h2>
        </div>
        <div class="layer-content">
          <p>Stephane's AI watch is continuous — X, Telegram, Reddit. Here are the open source models and projects that caught our attention, and why.</p>
          <div class="watch-grid">
            <div class="watch-item">
              <div class="watch-header">
                <span class="watch-name">Qwen3 / QwQ</span>
                <span class="watch-org">Alibaba Cloud</span>
              </div>
              <p>Long-form reasoning, solid coding. The only open source model ecosystem that rivals proprietary frontiers on technical benchmarks.</p>
            </div>
            <div class="watch-item">
              <div class="watch-header">
                <span class="watch-name">DeepSeek R1 / V3</span>
                <span class="watch-org" style="display:inline-flex;align-items:center;gap:0.35rem;">
                  <img src="https://cdn.simpleicons.org/deepseek/4D6BFE" alt="" class="watch-logo" loading="lazy" aria-hidden="true" onerror="this.style.display='none'" />
                  DeepSeek AI
                </span>
              </div>
              <p>Open weights, top-tier technical performance. Particularly interesting for analysis and coding tasks — trained at lower cost with innovative techniques.</p>
            </div>
            <div class="watch-item">
              <div class="watch-header">
                <span class="watch-name">Phi-4</span>
                <span class="watch-org" style="display:inline-flex;align-items:center;gap:0.35rem;">
                  <img src="https://cdn.simpleicons.org/microsoft/00A4EF" alt="" class="watch-logo" loading="lazy" aria-hidden="true" onerror="this.style.display='none'" />
                  Microsoft
                </span>
              </div>
              <p>The best example of "small but capable." 14B parameters that outperform models 3x larger on reasoning tasks. Ideal target for local inference.</p>
            </div>
            <div class="watch-item">
              <div class="watch-header">
                <span class="watch-name">SmolLM</span>
                <span class="watch-org" style="display:inline-flex;align-items:center;gap:0.35rem;">
                  <img src="https://cdn.simpleicons.org/huggingface/FFD21E" alt="" class="watch-logo" loading="lazy" aria-hidden="true" onerror="this.style.display='none'" />
                  HuggingFace
                </span>
              </div>
              <p>Ultra-compact models (135M-1.7B) designed for on-device inference. Our target for AIOps behavioral fine-tuning — small enough to run without a dedicated GPU.</p>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- Fine-tuning vision -->
    <section class="layer">
      <div class="container">
        <div class="layer-header">
          <img src="https://cdn.simpleicons.org/huggingface/FFD21E" alt="" class="tech-logo" loading="lazy" aria-hidden="true" onerror="this.style.display='none'" />
          <h2>Vision — sovereign fine-tuning</h2>
        </div>
        <div class="layer-content">
          <p>The next step: a model shaped for our infra, running locally with no external dependency. Not a model that <em>knows</em> the infra through its weights — facts change too fast — but a model that <strong>behaves like an ops engineer.</strong></p>
          <div class="finetune-flow">
            <div class="ft-step">
              <span class="ft-icon">01</span>
              <div>
                <h4>HuggingFace Pro</h4>
                <p>ZeroGPU (H100/H200) via Spaces — on-demand compute without buying a dedicated GPU</p>
              </div>
            </div>
            <div class="ft-arrow">→</div>
            <div class="ft-step">
              <span class="ft-icon">02</span>
              <div>
                <h4>Unsloth + LoRA</h4>
                <p>Efficient fine-tuning on <em>behavior</em>: ops diagnostics, tool use, concise tone</p>
              </div>
            </div>
            <div class="ft-arrow">→</div>
            <div class="ft-step">
              <span class="ft-icon">03</span>
              <div>
                <h4>GGUF quantization</h4>
                <p>Export the fine-tuned model in compact format for local inference</p>
              </div>
            </div>
            <div class="ft-arrow">→</div>
            <div class="ft-step">
              <span class="ft-icon">04</span>
              <div>
                <h4>Local Ollama</h4>
                <p>Silent and sovereign inference on the homelab — zero API cost</p>
              </div>
            </div>
          </div>
          <p class="finetune-note"><strong>Facts</strong> (IPs, service states, runbooks) stay in a dynamic RAG fed by <code>homelab-infra/</code>. Fine-tuning is not for memorizing — it is for forging the agent's character.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- Stats -->
    <StatsBar stats={[
      { number: '24 GB', label: 'VRAM RTX 3090' },
      { number: '3', label: 'APIs in prod' },
      { number: '6', label: 'MCP connected' },
      { number: '$0', label: 'cloud AI infra' },
    ]} />

    <!-- Crosslink symbiosis -->
    <section class="crosslink reveal">
      <div class="container">
        <a href="/symbiose" class="crosslink-block">
          <div>
            <h3>&#9670; The method</h3>
            <p>How we work together — least-privilege MCP, persistent memory, custom skills. The philosophy behind the AI ecosystem.</p>
          </div>
          <span class="crosslink-arrow">&#8594;</span>
        </a>
      </div>
    </section>
  </main>
</Base>

<style>
  .hero-mini {
    padding: 4rem 0 3rem;
  }

  .terminal-prompt {
    font-family: var(--font-mono);
    color: var(--color-accent);
    font-size: 0.95rem;
    margin-bottom: 0.75rem;
  }

  h1 {
    font-size: clamp(2rem, 5vw, 3rem);
    font-weight: 800;
    letter-spacing: -0.02em;
    line-height: 1.1;
    margin-bottom: 1rem;
  }

  .dot { color: var(--color-accent); }

  .subtitle {
    color: var(--color-text-muted);
    font-size: 1.1rem;
    max-width: 42rem;
  }

  /* Layers */
  .layer {
    padding: 3rem 0;
    border-top: 1px solid var(--color-border);
  }

  .layer-header {
    display: flex;
    align-items: center;
    gap: 1rem;
    margin-bottom: 1.5rem;
  }

  .layer-number {
    font-family: var(--font-mono);
    font-size: 0.85rem;
    color: var(--color-accent);
    font-weight: 700;
  }

  .layer-header h2 { font-size: 1.4rem; margin-bottom: 0; }

  .tech-logo {
    width: 1.4rem;
    height: 1.4rem;
    flex-shrink: 0;
  }

  .api-logo-img {
    width: 1.6rem;
    height: 1.6rem;
    flex-shrink: 0;
  }

  .watch-logo {
    width: 0.95rem;
    height: 0.95rem;
    flex-shrink: 0;
    vertical-align: middle;
  }

  .layer-content > p {
    color: var(--color-text-muted);
    max-width: 48rem;
    margin-bottom: 1.5rem;
    line-height: 1.7;
  }

  .layer-content > p strong { color: var(--color-text); }

  /* Specs */
  .specs { margin-bottom: 1.5rem; }

  .spec {
    display: flex;
    gap: 1rem;
    padding: 0.6rem 0;
    border-bottom: 1px solid var(--color-border);
    align-items: baseline;
  }

  .spec:last-child { border-bottom: none; }

  .spec-label {
    font-family: var(--font-mono);
    font-size: 0.8rem;
    color: var(--color-accent);
    min-width: 6rem;
    flex-shrink: 0;
  }

  .spec-value {
    font-size: 0.9rem;
    color: var(--color-text-muted);
  }

  /* Models grid */
  .models-grid {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: repeat(auto-fill, minmax(14rem, 1fr));
    gap: 1rem;
  }

  .model-group {
    background: var(--color-surface);
    border: 1px solid var(--color-border);
    border-radius: 6px;
    padding: 1.25rem;
  }

  .model-group h4 {
    font-size: 0.8rem;
    color: var(--color-accent);
    font-family: var(--font-mono);
    margin-bottom: 0.75rem;
  }

  .model-tags {
    display: flex;
    flex-wrap: wrap;
    gap: 0.4rem;
  }

  .model-tags span {
    font-family: var(--font-mono);
    font-size: 0.7rem;
    background: var(--color-bg);
    color: var(--color-text-muted);
    padding: 0.2rem 0.5rem;
    border-radius: 4px;
    border: 1px solid var(--color-border);
  }

  /* API cards */
  .api-grid {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: repeat(auto-fill, minmax(18rem, 1fr));
    gap: 1rem;
  }

  .api-card {
    background: var(--color-surface);
    border: 1px solid var(--color-border);
    border-radius: 8px;
    padding: 1.5rem;
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
    gap: 0.75rem;
  }

  .claude-card { border-top: 3px solid var(--color-accent); }
  .minimax-card { border-top: 3px solid #a855f7; }
  .groq-card { border-top: 3px solid #f59e0b; }

  .api-header {
    display: flex;
    justify-content: space-between;
    align-items: center;
  }

  .api-name {
    font-family: var(--font-mono);
    font-weight: 700;
    font-size: 1rem;
  }

  .api-role {
    font-size: 0.75rem;
    color: var(--color-text-muted);
    font-family: var(--font-mono);
  }

  .api-desc {
    font-size: 0.85rem;
    color: var(--color-text-muted);
    line-height: 1.5;
  }

  .api-tags {
    display: flex;
    flex-wrap: wrap;
    gap: 0.35rem;
    margin-top: auto;
  }

  .api-tags span {
    font-family: var(--font-mono);
    font-size: 0.7rem;
    background: var(--color-bg);
    color: var(--color-text-muted);
    padding: 0.15rem 0.4rem;
    border-radius: 3px;
    border: 1px solid var(--color-border);
  }

  /* Watch grid */
  .watch-grid {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: repeat(2, 1fr);
    gap: 1rem;
  }

  .watch-item {
    background: var(--color-surface);
    border: 1px solid var(--color-border);
    border-left: 3px solid var(--color-accent);
    border-radius: 6px;
    padding: 1.25rem;
  }

  .watch-header {
    display: flex;
    justify-content: space-between;
    align-items: baseline;
    margin-bottom: 0.6rem;
  }

  .watch-name {
    font-family: var(--font-mono);
    font-size: 0.9rem;
    font-weight: 700;
    color: var(--color-text);
  }

  .watch-org {
    font-size: 0.72rem;
    color: var(--color-text-muted);
  }

  .watch-item p {
    font-size: 0.83rem;
    color: var(--color-text-muted);
    line-height: 1.5;
  }

  /* Fine-tuning flow */
  .finetune-flow {
    display: flex;
    align-items: center;
    gap: 0.75rem;
    flex-wrap: wrap;
    margin-bottom: 1.5rem;
  }

  .ft-step {
    background: var(--color-surface);
    border: 1px solid var(--color-border);
    border-radius: 8px;
    padding: 1rem 1.25rem;
    display: flex;
    align-items: flex-start;
    gap: 0.75rem;
    flex: 1;
    min-width: 10rem;
  }

  .ft-icon {
    font-family: var(--font-mono);
    font-size: 0.8rem;
    color: var(--color-accent);
    font-weight: 700;
    flex-shrink: 0;
    margin-top: 0.1rem;
  }

  .ft-step h4 { font-size: 0.85rem; margin-bottom: 0.25rem; }

  .ft-step p {
    font-size: 0.75rem;
    color: var(--color-text-muted);
    line-height: 1.4;
  }

  .ft-arrow {
    color: var(--color-accent);
    font-family: var(--font-mono);
    font-size: 1.2rem;
    flex-shrink: 0;
  }

  .finetune-note {
    background: rgba(56, 189, 248, 0.05);
    border-left: 3px solid var(--color-accent);
    padding: 0.75rem 1rem;
    border-radius: 0 6px 6px 0;
    font-size: 0.85rem !important;
    color: var(--color-text-muted) !important;
    line-height: 1.6 !important;
    margin-bottom: 0 !important;
  }

  .finetune-note strong { color: var(--color-text) !important; }

  /* Crosslink */
  .crosslink { padding: 2rem 0 3rem; }

  .crosslink-block {
    display: flex;
    align-items: center;
    justify-content: space-between;
    gap: 2rem;
    padding: 1.5rem 2rem;
    border: 1px solid rgba(56, 189, 248, 0.2);
    border-radius: 8px;
    background: linear-gradient(135deg, rgba(56, 189, 248, 0.05), rgba(56, 189, 248, 0.02));
    text-decoration: none;
    color: inherit;
    transition: border-color 0.3s, box-shadow 0.3s;
  }

  .crosslink-block:hover {
    border-color: var(--color-accent);
    box-shadow: 0 0 20px rgba(56, 189, 248, 0.1);
    color: inherit;
  }

  .crosslink-block h3 {
    font-size: 1rem;
    color: var(--color-accent);
    margin-bottom: 0.5rem;
  }

  .crosslink-block p {
    font-size: 0.85rem;
    color: var(--color-text-muted);
    line-height: 1.5;
    max-width: 42rem;
  }

  .crosslink-arrow {
    font-size: 1.5rem;
    color: var(--color-accent);
    flex-shrink: 0;
  }

  @media (max-width: 640px) {
    .hero-mini { padding: 2rem 0 1.5rem; }
    h1 { font-size: clamp(1.5rem, 5vw, 2.5rem); }
    .subtitle { font-size: 0.95rem; }
    .spec { flex-direction: column; gap: 0.25rem; }
    .spec-label { min-width: unset; }
    .models-grid, .api-grid, .watch-grid, .details-grid { grid-template-columns: 1fr; gap: 0.75rem; }
    .model-group, .api-card, .watch-item, .detail { padding: 0.75rem 1rem; }
    .finetune-flow { flex-direction: column; }
    .ft-arrow { transform: rotate(90deg); }
    .ft-step { width: 100%; min-width: unset; padding: 0.75rem 1rem; }
    .crosslink-block { flex-direction: column; gap: 1rem; padding: 1.25rem; }
    .crosslink-block p { font-size: 0.82rem; }
    .layer-header { flex-wrap: wrap; gap: 0.5rem; }
  }
</style>
